<p>Answer to the exercise for the reader: &#8220;contrarianism&#8221; is the complement of &#8220;centrism&#8221;, but instead of trying to attract those who <em>agree</em> with the same things you do, you try to attract those who <em>disagree</em> with the same things you do.</p>

