<div id="c9">
<p>Independent views of any type (that is, views substantially different from the two party lines) are essentially useless in the US due to the spoiler effect which in turn is due to the simple majority voting scheme we use.  Switching to Condorcet or Austrlian-style voting would make such positions more tenable.  Until we do so, however, independent centrist candidates should be ignored or should instead co-opt the system by becoming the nominee of the party closer to their views.</p>

