<div id="c20">
<p>&#8220;Often &#8220;there is no universal right or wrong `answer&#8217;&#8221; is really a code for &#8216;actually there&#8217;s a whole lot of data to tell us what the right answer is, but looking at data is boring&#8217;&#8221;</p>

<p>Yes, I certainly agree that there are some issues where this is true (coming from <em>both</em> end of the political spectrum), but then aren&#8217;t you still blinded by your own personal biases?  What you consider to be a universal truth may be muddy to another.  That&#8217;s just how it is when dealing with human beings.</p>

